label("$\theta$", (0.3,0.3));
[/asy]

Then $\cos \theta = \frac{1}{3},$ so $\theta = \arccos \frac{1}{3}.$  By Pythagoras, the opposite side is $2 \sqrt{2},$ so $\tan \theta = \boxed{2 \sqrt{2}}.$

We have that $r = \sqrt{0^2 + 3^2} = 3.$  Also, if we draw the line connecting the origin and $(0,3),$ this line makes an angle of $\frac{\pi}{2}$ with the positive $x$-axis.

[asy]
unitsize(0.8 cm);

